            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Related: `ft_sql.txt` has stuff like\r\n```\r\nThese are maps which use populate the completion list using Vim's syntax\r\nhighlighting rules. >\r\n    <C-C>a\r\n<       - Displays all SQL syntax items. >\r\n```\r\n(note the inline list item) that is not recognized as codeblock.\r\n\r\nI seriously think that we need to significantly tighten up the spec, write the parser for that _and only that_, and fix the bundled help files once and for all (and make clear to plugins that if they want to have proper rendering in Neovim, they have to follow suit).",
